decision_conditions:
Condition : 3 - No demolition shall take place until a Demolition Management Plan has been submitted to, and approved in writing by, the local planning authority. The approved Plan shall be adhered to throughout the demolition period. The Plan shall include
�	site plan showing the position of the various elements required to support the demolition (welfare facilities, site hut/office);  
�	confirmation that a pre-start record of site conditions on the adjoining public highway will be undertaken with Hounslow Highways and a commitment to repair any damage caused;
�	details of the parking for site operatives and visitors (to be indicated on the site plan); 
�	loading and storage areas for the excavated materials; 
�	proposed washing facilities at the site exit and a commitment to sweep adjacent roads when required and at the request of the council;
�	measures to ensure the safety of all users of the public highway especially cyclists and pedestrians in the vicinity of the site and especially at the access;
�	Commitment to avoid attendance to the site by large vehicles (HGV) associated with the proposed works.
Reason: To ensure highway safety is maintained and preserved.
